CreatedDate.description: Read-only date and time of the object's creation.

CustomerKey.description: User-supplied unique identifier for an object within an object type (corresponds to the external key assigned to an object in the user interface).

ExistingUndeliverables.description: Indicates whether bounces occurred on previous send.

ExistingUnsubscribes.description: Indicates whether unsubscriptions occurred on previous send.

ForwardedEmails.description: Number of emails forwarded for a send.

HardBounces.description: Indicates number of hard bounces associated with a send.

ID.description: Read-only legacy identifier for an object. Not supported on all objects. Some objects use the ObjectID property as the Marketing Cloud unique ID.

InvalidAddresses.description: Specifies the number of invalid addresses associated with a send.

MissingAddresses.description: Specifies number of missing addresses encountered within a send.

ModifiedDate.description: Indicates the last time object information was modified.

NumberDelivered.description: Number of sent emails that did not bounce.

NumberSent.description: Number of emails actually sent as part of an email send. This number reflects all of the sent messages and may include bounced messages.

ObjectID.description: System-controlled, read-only text string identifier for object.

OtherBounces.description: Specifies number of Other-type bounces in a send.

PartnerProperties.description: Specifies key-value pairs of properties associated with an object.

SendID.description: Contains identifier for a specific send.

SoftBounces.description: Indicates number of soft bounces associated with a specific send.

UniqueClicks.description: Indicates number of unique clicks on message.

UniqueOpens.description: Indicates number of unique opens resulting from a triggered send.

Unsubscribes.description: Indicates the number of unsubscribe events associated with a send.
